  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6571 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma concentration (6560-6570 strikes holding -85M+ in amplifying GEX), dealers are forced to buy this bounce and will aggressively sell any dip back toward 6560. The breakout regime with -105B total GEX means dealer hedging will amplify moves in both directions, but the proximity to max negative gamma at 6560 creates a dangerous floor where selling pressure intensifies rapidly. Watch 6600 as the critical resistance where positive gamma flips dealers into selling mode, while any break below 6560 triggers accelerated dealer buying but in a destabilizing fashion.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect violent swings with strong support at 6560 but explosive moves if that breaks.",
